        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 18 at 5:11PM CDT by NWS Amarillo TX</headline>
        <description>At 510 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Dozier, or 13 miles southwest of Shamrock, moving west at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts of 50 to 55 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Samnorwood, Dozier, and Lutie.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
